<p>Therein lies the problem.  Why don&#8217;t the busybodies mind their own damn business and let people try to make what they want of their little part of the world.  Instead of forced relationships, allow people the opportunity to form voluntary relationships.  Introducing the force brought about through government only exacerbates problems between individuals, and groups of individuals.  That is the essence of libertarianism, voluntary society eschewing the use of violence to make people conform to other&#8217;s idea of normal.</p>
<p>Before you tell me it can&#8217;t work, tell me your personal cop&#8217;s name.  How much does the bastard weigh, and don&#8217;t you get tired of hauling his sorry ass around to keep you in line?</p>
